# Tailwind CSS Conventions

## Class Ordering (Logical Order)

Always order Tailwind classes in this sequence:

```vue
<template>
  <div
    class="
      <!-- 1. Layout & Positioning -->
      flex flex-col items-center justify-start
      absolute fixed relative sticky
      
      <!-- 2. Sizing -->
      w-full h-44 min-w-96 max-w-md
      
      <!-- 3. Spacing -->
      p-12 px-4 py-8 m-12 mx-auto gap-8
      
      <!-- 4. Borders -->
      border border-1 border-grey-200 rounded-lg
      
      <!-- 5. Background -->
      bg-core-white bg-grey-50
      
      <!-- 6. Text & Typography -->
      text-lg font-bold text-grey-500
      
      <!-- 7. Effects -->
      opacity-50 shadow-md
      
      <!-- 8. Interaction States (always last) -->
      hover:bg-blue-600
      focus:border-blue-600
      active:bg-blue-700
      disabled:bg-blue-200
    "
  >
```

## Design Tokens Usage

Use semantic tokens instead of hardcoded values:

```typescript
// GOOD - uses semantic tokens
class="bg-core-white text-grey-500 border-grey-200"
class="bg-semantic-error-200 hover:bg-semantic-error-300"
class="bg-semantic-success-200 text-core-white"

// BAD - hardcoded values
class="bg-white text-gray-500 border-gray-200"
class="bg-red-500 hover:bg-red-600"
class="bg-green-500 text-white"
```

## Semantic Color Tokens

| Token | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `bg-core-white` | White background |
| `text-grey-500` | Secondary text |
| `bg-semantic-error-200` | Danger/Error background |
| `bg-semantic-success-200` | Success background |
| `bg-semantic-warning-200` | Warning background |
| `bg-semantic-info-200` | Info/Primary background |

## Environment-Specific Sizing

```css
/* Frontoffice - smaller sizes */
.fz-button--frontoffice {
  @apply h-44 px-12 text-base;
}

/* Backoffice - larger sizes */
.fz-button--backoffice {
  @apply h-32 px-16 text-lg;
}
```

## Variant Class Pattern

```vue
<template>
  <button :class="buttonClasses">
    <slot />
  </button>
</template>

<script setup lang="ts">
const props = defineProps<{ variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' }>()

const variantClasses = {
  primary: 'bg-blue-500 text-white hover:bg-blue-600',
  secondary: 'bg-core-white text-grey-500 border-grey-200 hover:bg-grey-100'
}

const buttonClasses = computed(() => [
  'fz-button',
  variantClasses[props.variant]
])
</script>
```

## State Classes Order

When combining states, use this order:
```css
/* Correct order */
class="bg-blue-500 text-white h-44 px-12 gap-8 border-1 rounded-lg focus:bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 disabled:bg-blue-200"

/* Wrong order */
class="disabled:bg-blue-200 hover:bg-blue-600 focus:bg-blue-500 bg-blue-500"
```
